VSpirited concert
p3
sVnews
p4
VSreerama Gana Sabhaof Nallakuntahas organised a  vocal duet concert by Komanduri brothers, Krishna and Rajan, as part of its Sri Rama Koti Festival.The brothers are the sons and disciples of veteran vocalist-violinist Komanduri Seshadri. Amongst the two, Krishna is a noted violinist and a vocalist as well.  Rajan, an emerging violinist, followed his brother carefully and the duo presented a neat concert.The brothers concert  began with Purandaradasa&#8217;sJaya Jayain Nattai with little swaram in it. Vasantha was neatly elaborated by Krishna forRama Chandram Bhavayamiof Deekshitar, a rare song.Makela ra Vicharamuin Ravichandrika was rendered in a Dhuritha kalam with good swaram.Bantureethi koluvuin Hamsanadham was rendered with good synchronisation.Panthuvarali was chosen for a detailed essay of the ragam and Krishna&#8217;s knowledge was reflected in his approach. Ramadasu&#8217;sEnnaganu Ramabhajanawas voiced with strong swarams.Karnataka Devagandhari was the major attraction of the day and the ragam came out well forBhajare re Manasawith effective swarakalpana.The brothers performed with Seshadri on the violin and Vidya Sagar on the mridangam. Seshadri, a seasoned violinist, elevated the concert with his accompaniment and Sagar was good.The brothers concluded their duet withRamachandrudithedeof Annamacharya and finallyRamachandra Dayain Surati.The two showed good spirit in their debut concert and, with sustained effort and coordination, can become a competent performers in the near future.
